# ==============================================================================
# DEPRECATED: This file is no longer the primary config source.
#
# All environment variables are now managed from the ROOT .env file:
#   → ../../.env  (relative to this directory)
#
# This file is kept ONLY for local development without Docker.
# If you run `python manage.py runserver` directly, Django reads from here.
# For Docker, the root docker-compose.yml injects env from the root .env.
# ==============================================================================

# To use: copy the relevant backend variables from the root .env.example
# or create a symlink:   mklink .env ..\..\\.env   (Windows)
#                         ln -sf ../../.env .env   (Linux/Mac)